Subdirectories within the package name directory are actually not supported;
symlinks are not supported.

In order to make subdirectories kind of work, use hardlinks to the package name
directory.

Example:

    $ LS_COLORS="" tree -FCaugp --inodes x11-misc
    [1310186 drwx------ portage  portage ]  x11-misc/
    └── [1324471 drwx------ portage  portage ]  parcellite-1.2.1/
        ├── [1328255 drwx------ portage  portage ]  fix_too_many_arguments/
        │   └── [1324472 drwx------ portage     portage    ]  src/
        │       └── [1308367 -rw------- portage  portage ]  main.c.patch
        └── [1308367 -rw------- portage  portage ]  main.c.patch

    Both "main.c.patch" files have the same inode number.

Every file and directory must have the following permissions, in order to apply
patches successfully:

    * Owner: portage
    * Group: portage
    * Umask: 0077
        * files: 0600
        * directories: 0700
